3. Calculate the probability of each value separately: $P(X=10)= rac{3}{10}× rac{3}{10}= rac{9}{100}$, $P(X=12)=2× rac{3}{10}× rac{7}{10}= rac{21}{50}$, $P(X=14)= rac{7}{10}× rac{7}{10}= rac{49}{100}$;
4. List the distribution column of X;
5. Calculate $EX=10× rac{9}{100}+12× rac{21}{50}+14× rac{49}{100}$ according to the mathematical expectation formula and simplify to get the result.

